{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EFQ3qchiyxa6LTLmpQoc7g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is in place and verified. Here's the summary:\n\n**What's configured:**\n\nThe `elasticsearch-https` Ingress in the `elasticsearch` namespace is configured with:\n- **Ingress class:** `nginx`\n- **Host:** `es.example.com` with TLS secret `es-ingress-tls`\n- **Backend:** `es-http:9200`\n- **Key annotations:**\n  - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/backend-protocol: HTTPS` — tells nginx to speak HTTPS to the ES backend (ES only listens on TLS)\n  - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/force-ssl-redirect: \"true\"` + `ssl-redirect: \"true\"` — HTTP is never passed through\n  - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/proxy-ssl-verify: \"off\"` — skips verification of ES's self-signed cert\n\n**Verified behavior:**\n- `https://es.example.com` → reaches Elasticsearch, returns `401` (auth required — ES is live and responding)\n- `http://es.example.com` → `308 Permanent Redirect` to HTTPS, never touches ES\n\n**Cluster health:** all 3 ES pods running, ingress-nginx controller running, no restarts."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1167,"cache_read_input_tokens":36305,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1167},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9547b0c-ebb4-415d-8a3c-6a19f6508517","uuid":"51bd03b0-f918-4e00-8c04-b96bca6b50e6","request_id":"req_011CcfspTmJzkxifAzmSerEH"}
